page.title: 01North Lynn & South Wootton
page.content: Our block covers part of North Lynn, which is a housing and industrial estate and this is linked by the North Lynn bypass to South Wootton village. This used to be totally separate from King's Lynn, as the railway line separated the two. When the bypass was built, eleven years ago, the two have gradually grown together. This is an arable farming area and many of the industries are related to farming e.g. food processing .King's Lynn also has a thriving dock and therefore many factories are related to goods imported and exported from the docks e.g.cars and fuel. The population of North Lynn is mainly Norfolk born and bred,whereas the population of South Wootton come from many areas of the country.
